<table class="material-table">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Material</th>
      <th>English Description</th>
      <th>Mandarin (简体 / Pinyin)</th>
      <th>Mandarin Description</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Tungsten carbide</strong></td>
      <td>Extremely hard, very wear-resistant; used for long-life bits and tip inserts; brittle compared with steel.</td>
      <td>硬质合金（碳化钨） / yìngzhì héjīn (tànhuà wū)</td>
      <td>极高硬度与耐磨性，常用于高寿命/高磨损的批头或刀尖插入件；较脆。</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Ceramic (alumina)</strong></td>
      <td>Very hard, electrically insulating and corrosion-resistant; brittle; used when insulation or non-magnetic properties are needed.</td>
      <td>陶瓷（氧化铝） / táocí (yǎnghuà lǚ)</td>
      <td>非常硬且电绝缘、耐腐蚀，适用于需要绝缘或无磁的专用场合，但脆性大。</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>S2 tool steel</strong></td>
      <td>High toughness and wear resistance; common for impact and heavy-duty bits after heat treatment.</td>
      <td>S2 工具钢 / S2 gōngjù gāng</td>
      <td>韧性与耐磨性高，常用于冲击/重载批头，淬火回火后可达较高硬度。</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>High-carbon, quenched &amp; tempered steel</strong></td>
      <td>Heat-treated for high hardness and wear resistance; used in quality blades and bits.</td>
      <td>高碳钢（淬火回火） / gāo tàn gāng (cuìhuǒ huíhuǒ)</td>
      <td>通过热处理获得高硬度与耐磨性，常用于高质量刀锋与批头。</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Chrome-molybdenum (Cr-Mo) steel</strong></td>
      <td>Tough and impact-resistant; used for impact drivers and heavy tools; can be heat treated for higher hardness.</td>
      <td>铬钼钢 / gè mó gāng</td>
      <td>韧性好、耐冲击，常用于冲击起子和重载工具；可热处理提高硬度。</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Chromium-vanadium (Cr-V) steel</strong></td>
      <td>Common general-purpose tool steel; Cr and V improve strength, hardness and toughness.</td>
      <td>铬钒钢 / gè fán gāng</td>
      <td>常见通用工具钢，铬与钒提高强度、硬度与韧性，家用与车用起子常见。</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Hardened stainless (e.g., 410/420)</strong></td>
      <td>Good corrosion resistance; some grades can be heat treated to moderate hardness; generally softer than high-alloy tool steels.</td>
      <td>410/420 不锈钢 / 410/420 bùxiù gāng</td>
      <td>抗腐蚀性好，某些牌号可热处理到中等硬度；通常比高合金工具钢软。</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Titanium / titanium alloy</strong></td>
      <td>Lightweight, corrosion-resistant and non-magnetic; lower hardness and wear resistance than tool steels; for specialty uses.</td>
      <td>钛 / 钛合金 / tài / tài héjīn</td>
      <td>轻、耐腐蚀、非磁性，但硬度与耐磨性低于工具钢，常用于轻量或要求非磁性的专用工具。</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
